							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/edward-simon/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picture1-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picture1-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Ed Simon" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/edward-simon/">Ed Simon</a></h6>
										Ed Simon is the Public Humanities Special Faculty in the English Department of Carnegie Mellon University, a staff writer for Lit Hub, and the editor of <em>Belt Magazine</em>. His most recent book is <em>Devil's Contract: The History of the Faustian Bargain</em>, the first comprehensive, popular account of that subject.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="http://edsimon.org" target="_blank" class="external">http://edsimon.org</a>
